    "RAG involves an initial retrieval step where the LLMs query an external data source to obtain relevant information before proceeding to answer questions or generate text (GAO et al., 2024).",
    "RAG operates in two main phases: retrieval and content generation.",
    "involves encoding documents and user input into vectors of real numbers, commonly referred to as embeddings.",
    "These document embeddings are subsequently stored in a vector database.",
    "Algorithms search for and retrieve relevant snippets of information based on the user's prompt or question in vector database."
